data.meta_description: Isabella (Isabelle) "The Fair" "The She-Wolf" of France, Queen Consort of England was born on March 17, 1292 in Paris, Paris, Île-de-France, France, daughter of Philippe IV "The Fair" Capet of France, King of France and Jeanne I Queen of Navarre, Queen of England, Countess of Champagne. She was married on January 24, 1308 in Boulogne Cathedral to Edward II Plantagenet, King of England, they had 4 children. She died on August 22, 1358 in Castle Rising, Norfolk, England. This information is part of Family tree Cromer/Russell/Buck/Pratt by Elizabeth Cromer on Genealogy Online.
